Cook chicken in oil in large skillet, 5 minutes; remove and set aside. Add peppers, onion, mushrooms and garlic; cook 5 minutes or until tender. Add chicken. Mix tomato paste with 1 can water; add to skillet with diced tomatoes and oregano. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Simmer 15 minutes. Add shrimp; cook 5 minutes or until shrimp are just pink. Serve over rice, if desired.